This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the evaluation of open-domain dialog systems. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as these fields are closely related to natural language processing and dialog systems. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SD (Sound) as dialog systems often involve speech recognition and synthesis. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as the paper discusses the use of human annotations for evaluation.
